Rating: 3
I found another recipe for this in a french provincial cookbook. You ad just enough water to cover the carrots, and then salt the water. Cook until ALMOST all the water is absorbed. THEN add the sugar and butter, and over high heta, toss until coated and the rest of the water is gone. Then add fresh or dried dill, just a bit, and fresh parsley if you have it (if you only have dried, leave it out).

Rating: 3
I thought this was a very tasty way to bring out the natural sweetness of the carrots, I think next time I would add just a tad more butter. The best thing about this recipe is that it is so simple to make, almost as simple as the recipe for 'Salted Boiling Water'.I would make this again, it's a keeper.

Rating: 3
I sliced baby carrots lengthwise and cooked them in salted butter, water from a Brita filter and brown sugar. I thought it would turn out like candied carrots, but this is much more delicate. It was a good contrast to the spicier Arugula Vichyssoise I made for the same meal. Maybe a light dash of Ginger would be good in it.

